                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.751/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Governor of New York</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Governor</hi>: I am in receipt of your letter of
                    the 24th in which you advise me that the measure concerning which I wrote you on
                    the 19th was vetoed by you. I believe your action will save the Federal
                    Government very serious embarrassment and I heartily thank you for the prompt
                    and wise course which you have taken in regard to the proposed legislation.</p>
                <p>With warm regards [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
